## Best Practices

### DO ✅

```ruby
# Test critical user paths
test "user can complete signup and create first article"

# Use descriptive test names
test "admin can delete any article"

# Test happy path and error cases
test "shows error when article creation fails"

# Use helper methods for common actions
sign_in_as @user

# Test one workflow per test
test "creating and publishing article"

# Wait for elements when needed
assert_selector ".result", wait: 5
```

### DON'T ❌

```ruby
# Don't test every possible interaction
# Focus on critical user paths

# Don't make tests too long
# Split complex flows into multiple tests

# Don't forget to sign in when needed
# Many actions require authentication

# Don't use hard-coded sleeps
sleep 2  # Bad!
assert_selector ".result", wait: 2  # Good!

# Don't test CSS styling
# Focus on functionality
```

---

## Running System Tests

```bash
# Run all system tests
rails test:system

# Run specific test file
rails test:system test/system/articles_test.rb

# Run specific test
rails test:system test/system/articles_test.rb:10

# Run with visible browser (not headless)
CI=false rails test:system

# Run with screenshots on failure
rails test:system
```

